From: Bo-Cun Chen <bc-bocun.chen@mediatek.com>
Subject: net: ethernet: mtk_eth_soc: add mux cleanup to mtk_remove

Add mtk_release_all_muxes() call to mtk_remove() to properly clean up
passive mux resources when the driver is removed.

Split from 999-eth-01 due to line number divergence between Sinovoip
6.6 and vanilla 6.12 kernel at the mtk_remove location.

Ported from Sinovoip/MTK 999-2708 (kernel 6.6) to kernel 6.12.

Signed-off-by: Bo-Cun Chen <bc-bocun.chen@mediatek.com>
---
 drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.c | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)


--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/mediatek/mtk_eth_soc.c
@@ -5998,6 +5998,7 @@ static void mtk_remove(struct platform_device *pdev)
 	mtk_cleanup(eth);
 	free_netdev(eth->dummy_dev);
 	mtk_mdio_cleanup(eth);
+	mtk_release_all_muxes(eth);
 }

